The paper deals with lower bounds on communication complexity in distributed-memory parallel machines, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The specific problems studied in the paper, such as matrix multiplication, sorting, and FFT, are also relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Scientific Computing (cs.SC), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
